The acting manager of the Moretele Local Municipality in the North West has died. The municipality has confirmed that Thabo Makwela died in hospital on Saturday. Makwela, and two other municipal officials earlier tested positive for COVID-19. One is still in hospital and the other is in self- isolation. The municipal offices have been closed but municipal spokesperson, Mothupi Malebye, has assured the public that the delivery of basic services will not be disrupted. “We just want to confirm the loss of acting municipality manager, Mr Thabo Ben Makwela, the mayor of Moretele Local Municipality Makinta Andries Monaheng, has confirmed that, and as municipality we are going to take a responsibility to bury that man with dignity, and may his soul rest in peace.” Latest COVID-19 statistics in South Africa: 6 415 824 994 911 839 194 129 196 26 521 865 715 As at 26 December 2020 37 817 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); COVID-19 STATISTICS IN SOUTH AFRICA sabcnews.com |  SABC News Channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 18 0250 165 988 22 392 34 723 UNALLOCATED 0 AS AT 26 DECEMBER 2020 6802 543 638 DEATHS 2152 6162 5317 3958 577 CONFIRMED CASES | 994 911 DEATHS | 26 521 TESTS CONDUCTED | 6 415 824 RECOVERIES | 839 194 372 86163 27 2504 38 404 24791 19 4174  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 61 685 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://